description.narrative: IR1 on MCH: By 2015, maternal and child health inequities are reduced and intervention coverage is improved through increasingly standardized and evidence-based health policies, communication for development (C4D) approaches, service delivery and monitoring & evaluation (M&E)., which contributes to Access To Justice, Adolescent Health And Nutrition, Birth Registration, Child Health, Cross-Sectoral Communication For Development, Cross-Sectoral Early Childhood Development, Cross-Sectoral Monitoring, Data And Situation Analyses, Cross-Sectoral Planning And Programme Reviews, Early Childhood Development, Health Systems Strengthening, Health â€“ General, Hiv Prevention, Immunization, Maternal And Newborn Health, Micronutrients, Pmtct And Infant Male Circumcision, Polio Eradication, Prevention Of Stunting And Other Forms Of Malnutrition, Treatment And Care Of Children Living With Hiv, Treatment Of Severe Acute Malnutrition, Unicef Capacity For Supply And Logistics. UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: By 2015, children and women in China, particularly the poor and vulnerable, will enjoy a better health and nutrition status, and protection from impoverishment due to ill health.
